   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">You can analyze campaigns by comments for the campaigns  in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ACCEPTING COMMENTS</uicontrol> status.</context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Home</uicontrol> page, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Home</uicontrol>, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">All Campaigns</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">All Campaigns</uicontrol> page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Your campaigns</uicontrol> section, select the appropriate campaign in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ACCEPTING COMMENTS</uicontrol> status.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">View</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Campaign Details</uicontrol> page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To analyze all the comments for the campaign from the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">COMMENTS</uicontrol> tab, perform the following steps:</cmd>
            <substeps class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">COMMENTS</uicontrol> tab.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Comments</uicontrol> section displays the list of comments given by the general public for an appropriate project.</info>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">You can filter the comments based on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">User</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Project</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Category</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Sentiment</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Date</uicontrol>, and <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Responses</uicontrol>.<note class="- topic/note "> You are notified through the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Notifications</uicontrol> icon whenever any comment is received.</note>
                  </info>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To analyze all the comments for the campaign from the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ANALYTICS</uicontrol> tab, perform the following steps:</cmd>
            <substeps class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ANALYTICS</uicontrol> tab.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Campaign Analytics</uicontrol> page is displayed.</info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">CAMPAIGN BREAKDOWN</uicontrol> to view various portlets that provides analysis of the campaign.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The user can see portlets such as sentiment breakdown, word clouds, breakdown of public comments over time, participation trend, top positive and negative comments, breakdown of comments by category, and breakdown of comments by rating.<note class="- topic/note "> You can select the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">PROJECT BREAKDOWN</uicontrol> tab to view insights of comments for a project.</note>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To view further analysis of the comments in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Comments Overview</uicontrol> portlet, perform the following steps:</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Click the progress bar of <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Positive</uicontrol>.</p>
                           <p class="- topic/p ">A detailed insight of all the positive comments is displayed.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">To view another comment type, click the tabs next to <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Comments Overview</uicontrol>.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">To reply, select a comment and click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Reply</uicontrol>.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To return to the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">CAMPAIGN BREAKDOWN</uicontrol> page, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Back</uicontrol>.</cmd>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
      </steps>
